headline: Copart (NASDAQ:CPRT) Reports Sales Below Analyst Estimates In Q1 Earnings
summary: Online vehicle auction company Copart (NASDAQ:CPRT) missed Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q1 CY2025, but sales rose 7.5% year on year to $1.21 billion. Its GAAP profit of $0.42 per share was in line with analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: Billionaire Jamie Dimon Still Believes America Is Worth Investing In, Despite Trump Tariffs and Market Fluctuations. Should You Buy These 3 U.S. Stocks in 2025?
summary: Jamie Dimon has some scary things to say about the economy and the stock market, but his comments should be taken in context.  In the event that there are storms brewing on the horizon, investors will appreciate the dependability of these three U.S. stocks.  On May 19, JPMorgan Chase had an investor-day presentation and billionaire CEO Jamie Dimon had a lot to say about the economy, global trade, and investing.
